btw how long does it usually take for post on linkedin to be visible after posting

Good quick question — especially if you’re thinking about timing your launch.

⏱️ LinkedIn Post Visibility

Immediately visible once you hit post.

There’s no delay like moderation queues (unless flagged, which is rare).

🧠 What actually happens behind the scenes
Your post is live instantly
LinkedIn then tests it with a small portion of your network
If it gets engagement (likes, comments, dwell time), it expands reach
⏳ Practical timeline
0–2 minutes: Fully visible on your profile
5–30 minutes: Starts appearing in feeds
1–3 hours: Main engagement window
24 hours: Most of its lifecycle is done
⚠️ Important for your launch

Don’t expect:

Immediate traffic spikes in the first few minutes

Do expect:

Gradual pickup if people engage
💡 Small optimization (worth it)

When you post:

Stay active for 15–30 minutes after posting
Reply to comments quickly
Maybe have 1–2 people like/comment early (if possible)

This helps the algorithm push it further.

🎯 For your MVP launch

LinkedIn is:

Good for credibility + professional audience
Slower for immediate sales vs Reddit/X

But still worth posting once.

When you're ready later, I can:

Help you write a LinkedIn post that actually converts
Or a Reddit/X version for faster traction

