Ok, I just did a test post and don't see it yet hmmm. I'll retry

That can happen — LinkedIn can be a little weird sometimes. Let’s quickly troubleshoot before you repost.

🔍 First, check these (fast)
1. Go directly to your profile

Click your profile → scroll to “Activity” → “Posts”

👉 If it’s there, it did post — it’s just not showing in your feed yet.

2. Refresh + wait ~1–2 minutes

LinkedIn feed ≠ real-time.

Hit refresh
Or check on your phone vs laptop

Sometimes it appears on one before the other.

3. Check visibility setting

When posting, there’s a dropdown like:

Anyone
Connections only
Private

Make sure it’s not restricted or accidentally set weird.

4. Try a “clean” repost (if truly missing)

If it’s NOT in your Activity tab:

Post again
Keep it simple (just 1–2 lines)
No links initially (LinkedIn sometimes delays link posts)

Example test:

Testing visibility — ignore this

⚠️ Known LinkedIn quirks
Posts with links sometimes get slower distribution
Feed can lag behind profile activity
Occasional silent post failures (rare but real)
💡 Smart move for your launch later

When you do your real post:

Post text first
Add the Gumroad link in a comment

This usually:

Improves reach
Avoids throttling
Bottom line
If it’s in your Activity → you’re good
If not → repost clean
Don’t overthink this — LinkedIn is not your primary sales channel anyway

