another thing before, what is the best way to remove emails in bulk from my gmail account or even entirely?

Good question — and there are fast, controlled ways to do this without nuking something important.

I’ll give you 3 levels, from safe → aggressive.

🟢 OPTION 1: Bulk Delete by Category (Safest & Fastest)
Example: Promotions / Social (low risk)
Go to Gmail
Click Promotions tab

In search bar type:

category:promotions
Click the checkbox at top (selects ~50 emails)

Click:

“Select all conversations that match this search”

Hit Delete

💥 This deletes thousands instantly.

🟡 OPTION 2: Delete by Sender or Pattern (Targeted)
Example:
from:noreply

or

unsubscribe

Steps:

Search
Select all
Delete

Other powerful filters:

older_than:1y
larger:5M
has:attachment

👉 You can combine:

category:promotions older_than:6m
🔴 OPTION 3: Full Inbox Clean Sweep (Aggressive)

If you want near-reset:

Step 1:

Search:

in:inbox
Step 2:
Select all

Click:

“Select all conversations in inbox”

Delete
Step 3:

Go to Trash → Empty Trash

⚠️ This is permanent after 30 days (or immediately if emptied)

⚡ PRO MOVE (Best Balance)

Do this combo:

Delete:

category:promotions
category:social

Then:

older_than:1y
Then clean inbox manually

You’ll remove 80–90% of clutter fast.

🧠 Important Tip (Saves Future Pain)

Before deleting everything:

Search:

is:starred

Or:

label:important

Make sure nothing critical is there.

🚀 Automation (Optional but powerful)

After cleanup:

Create filter:
If email contains “unsubscribe”
→ auto-label or archive
Bottom Line
Fastest safe cleanup → category:promotions
Most control → search filters
Nuclear reset → in:inbox delete all

